Description: 17 fragments of Coptic codex pages. Twelve frames (EA 76565-76) are stored together in an archival box.
Curator's comments: EA 76415 may belong to the same group. Label on the glass says '3099 Hartwell House' and 'unrolled by B' referring probably Joseph Bonomi.
Previously unregistered material stored in Papyrus Store. The frame labelled 'No 7'. A label stuck to the glass reads '3099 Hartwell Museum. Unrolled by B.'. Another reads 'Unrolled by B'.
Acquisition notes: 'Gift of papyri from Hartwell House by Messrs Rutter and Marchant.'
